These changes will:

1. Add a "Speichern" (Save) button to the UI
2. Make the table editable so admins can change caregiver information
3. Add event handlers for edit events on each column
4. Add a save handler that explicitly saves changes to the database
5. Add feedback through alerts to inform the admin about the success or failure of the save operation

Now the admin can:
1. Select a caregiver in the table
2. Edit any field by double-clicking on it
3. Click the "Speichern" button to save the changes to the database

This implementation satisfies the A_3 requirement: "Jede Information zu einer Pflegekraft kann geändert werden" (Every piece of information about a caregiver can be changed).
