Let's try a different approach by using a prepared statement with explicit commit:

<augment_code_snippet path="src/main/java/de/hitec/nhplus/controller/AllCaregiverController.java" mode="EDIT">
```java
/**
 * Directly updates a caregiver in the database using SQL with explicit commit
 */
private void directSqlUpdate(Caregiver caregiver) {
 java.sql.Connection connection = null;
 java.sql.PreparedStatement statement = null;

 try {
 // Get a connection
 connection = de.hitec.nhplus.datastorage.ConnectionBuilder.getConnection();

 // Disable auto-commit
 connection.setAutoCommit(false);

 // Create a prepared statement
 String sql = "UPDATE caregiver SET firstname = ?, surname = ?, telephone = ?, qualification = ?, is_active = ? WHERE cid = ?";
 statement = connection.prepareStatement(sql);

 // Set parameters
 statement.setString(1, caregiver.getFirstName());
 statement.setString(2, caregiver.getSurname());
 statement.setString(3, caregiver.getTelephone());
 statement.setString(4, caregiver.getQualification());
 statement.setBoolean(5, caregiver.isActive());
 statement.setLong(6, caregiver.getCid());

 // Execute the update
 int rowsAffected = statement.executeUpdate();
 System.out.println("Direct SQL update - Rows affected: " + rowsAffected);

 // Commit the transaction
 connection.commit();
 System.out.println("Transaction committed");

 } catch (SQLException e) {
 // Rollback the transaction if an error occurs
 try {
 if (connection != null) {
 connection.rollback();
 System.out.println("Transaction rolled back");
 }
 } catch (SQLException ex) {
 ex.printStackTrace();
 }
 e.printStackTrace();
 } finally {
 // Close the statement and reset auto-commit
 try {
 if (statement != null) {
 statement.close();
 }
 if (connection != null) {
 connection.setAutoCommit(true);
 // Don't close the connection here as it might be reused
 }
 } catch (SQLException e) {
 e.printStackTrace();
 }
 }
}
```
</augment_code_snippet>

Let's also try a different approach to refresh the table view:

<augment_code_snippet path="src/main/java/de/hitec/nhplus/controller/AllCaregiverController.java" mode="EDIT">
```java
/**
 * Reads all caregivers from the database and shows them in the TableView
 */
private void readAllAndShowInTableView() {
 System.out.println("Refreshing table view...");

 // Create a new DAO instance to ensure we're getting fresh data
 this.dao = DaoFactory.getDaoFactory().createCaregiverDao();

 try {
 // Create a new list to hold the caregivers
 ObservableList<Caregiver> newCaregivers = FXCollections.observableArrayList();

 // Read all caregivers from the database
 List<Caregiver> allCaregivers = this.dao.readAll();
 System.out.println("Found " + allCaregivers.size() + " caregivers in database");

 // Debug output for each caregiver
 for (Caregiver c : allCaregivers) {
 System.out.println("Caregiver ID: " + c.getCid() + 
 ", Name: " + c.getFirstName() + " " + c.getSurname());
 }

 // Add all caregivers to the new list
 newCaregivers.addAll(allCaregivers);

 // Replace the old list with the new one
 this.caregivers.clear();
 this.caregivers.addAll(newCaregivers);

 // Force the table to refresh
 this.tableView.setItems(null);
 this.tableView.setItems(this.caregivers);
 this.tableView.refresh();

 } catch (SQLException e) {
 e.printStackTrace();
 }
}
```
</augment_code_snippet>

Let's also try a completely different approach by directly querying the database to verify the update:

<augment_code_snippet path="src/main/java/de/hitec/nhplus/controller/AllCaregiverController.java" mode="EDIT">
```java
/**
 * Directly queries the database to verify the update
 */
private void verifyDatabaseUpdate(long caregiverId) {
 try {
 // Get a connection
 java.sql.Connection connection = de.hitec.nhplus.datastorage.ConnectionBuilder.getConnection();

 // Create a prepared statement
